modules.description: This module converts Markdown documents into HTML elements using customizable renderers for links, images, and preformatted blocks. It operates on Markdown data types like `paragraph`, `par_text`, and `text`, producing structured HTML elements such as paragraphs, lists, and headings. Use it to generate HTML from Markdown content with fine-grained control over element rendering.

This module processes text lines into structured Markdown elements by parsing paragraphs, lists, quotes, and links, using types like headings, references, and parsing state. It handles string manipulation, indentation detection, and buffer management to convert raw input into organized document components. Applications include rendering Markdown to HTML, analyzing syntax structures, or building static content generators.
